text: Deč () is a village in Serbia. It is situated in the Pećinci municipality, in the Srem District, Vojvodina province. The village has a Serb ethnic majority and a population numbering 1,499 people (2011). ==See also== * List of cities, towns and villages in Vojvodina * List of places in Serbia Category:Populated places in Syrmia Category:Populated places in Srem District Category:Pećinci hr:Šimanovci
